Caledonia_Township,_Shiawassee_County,_Michigan
footnotes                 Caledonia Charter Township is a township of Shiawassee County in the state of Michigan.  The population was 4,427 at the 2000 census.Communities*Middletown is an community within the township between Corunna and Owosso.(shiawasseehistory.com Village and City Histories of Shiawassee County, Michigan)()*Kerby is an community within the township on Kerby Road.  State maps place it at Serr Road(SHIAWASSEE County Map. J. Shively.  State of Michigan Department of Information Technology Technology Center for Genographic Information.  September 2007.) while the Federal government place it on Shipman Road from Kerby Road., ()GeographyAccording to the States Census Bureau, the township has a total area of , of which,  of it is land and  of it (0.38%) is water.DemographicsAs of the census of 2000, there were 4,427 people, 1,712 households, and 1,287 families residing in the township.  The density was 139.8 per square mile (54.0/km).  There were 1,794 housing units at an average density of 56.7 per square mile (21.9/km).  The racial makeup of the township was 97.24% White, 0.14% African American, 0.32% Native American, 0.61% Asian, 0.02% Pacific Islander, 0.68% from other races, and 0.99% from two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race were 1.65% of the population.There were 1,712 households out of which 32.2% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 63.4% were married couples living together, 8.2% had a female householder with no husband present, and 24.8% were non-families. 20.9% of all households were made up of individuals and 10.1% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.  The average household size was 2.58 and the average family size was 2.97.In the township the population was spread out with 24.2% under the age of 18, 7.4% from 18 to 24, 28.2% from 25 to 44, 27.0% from 45 to 64, and 13.2% who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 40 years. For every 100 females there were 97.9 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 95.3 males.The median income for a household in the township was $42,139, and the median income for a family was $50,564. Males had a median income of $40,483 versus $26,971 for females. The capita income for the township was $19,385.  About 5.7% of families and 5.7% of the population were below the line, including 3.1% of those under age 18 and 10.0% of those age 65 or over.  Joseph W. DeCaire (D), currently serves as the Caledonia Charter Township Supervisor, a position he was elected to in November 2006. See also *Mining Company  Michigans first coal mine. References de Caledonia (condado de Shiawassee, Mchigan)
